name: Ron Zaras

social_posts.post_text:
Man. What I would give to properly say “thank you” in person right now.

For my career. 

For all the life advice. 

For all the times you took to really, genuinely explain why my crop/kerning/coloring/messaging sucked (and how to make it better next time)

For giving @ellebeesee and I an open door to your home when we needed one most.

For showing me the pride that comes with real fatherhood.

And for the wildest journey in motorsports and life I could have ever imagined. 

Fuck, I wish we were editing photos over Nandos together right now. 

You will be missed dearly.

It was a pretty rare occasion to get our core crew in photos together over the last 12 years… always makes me wish we had more. And ever thankful to those that snapped these shots, like @blabacphoto, @larry_chen_foto, @mckleinphotography, @tony_harmer, and of course that random Aussie dude who caught us photobombing a KISS photoshoot. 

Life lesson. Take more photos with your friends.
We present you “Lake Hoonigan”… @roncar taking the @subaru_usa BRZ for some wet terrain testing 🏄‍♂️

IG’s accuracy on pacenotes 🎯

Did my second rally sprint last weekend, first time ever writing and competing with my own two-pass notes. Learned a ton with @rally.kj in the hot seat. Blew some shit up too, so we only got two clean stages over the weekend - but at least we ended up being fastest overall on those. 

Big up to @rallyready, @texas_dave and his crew for putting on these events, easiest way to get into rally ever.

New series out now on YT: This vs. Dahm! You know I had to bring the FD out to set for some side-by-side rollers. It’s wild to see the differences from the original bodywork.

Thanks to @hatch.jpg for snapping these. 

I couldn’t be more hyped for @robdahm and @fabricationfather for how far they’ve been able to take this build. 

All the way back in 2014, when I was full time at Hoonigan Racing Div., Rob sent an email over to us asking if we could share the dimensions, specs, and other build info on the Hoonicorn when we first released it. We had no idea who this “Rob Dahm” guy was, and had just gone through two years of developing the car on our own with RTR vehicles. We weren’t about to give all that up for a random mystery internet person 😂

You know the rest of the story. Rob doubled down, measured pixels online, and set out on a career-making spirit journey just to make his dream come alive. Now he’s ripping savagely fast passes in the car, and is just getting started with its future. 

I typed all this out really, just to say - fuck yeah Rob. Never stop.

Somehow this is the most reliable car I have right now 😂

I added this @greddyperformance v mount setup recently, and it completely changed the car. Still on the stock twins right now, but it’s the perfect ripper. 

Still has AC too… absolutely crucial. 

#falkentire #azenisrt615kplus

At long last - the Evo is really coming back!

This thing has been slowly building up the background over the last few years. After it got wrecked in 2017 and needed a whole new front end/chassis leg, I decided to go head first  into a Gymkhana Grid style build, to eventually compete in the European Gauntlet. The build has taken me long enough that now, Gymkhana is coming back to the U.S. I’ll count that as a win 😅

Big thanks to @horns_collisioncenter for making the chassis straight again, Roni at @speedlab_inc for being my guide on the perfect engine build, and a bunch of great tech info from guys at @garrettmotion and @fullracemotorsports. Excited to see what this thing can put down, so I can do it some justice at the track.

Second time on our show This vs. That with the FD. Now with a little more spice thrown in: @greddyperformance v-mount kit, ported wastegates, fuel pump and a Power FC. That’s it. 
Such a dramatic different in driving experience now… aka, it’s finally fun outside of a canyon road.

When @mgcharoudin says “don’t lift, don’t brake”  at 100+ on your out-lap at the Nurburgring 😂

Out of our last three trips to Germany, @vin_tra and I have done zero hotlaps on the ‘ring; so we made it a mission to at least get one afternoon session in this week. But, thanks to a big wreck just as we showed up, that turned into one hectic lap each in the @apexnuerburg GTI. Still 100% worth the two hour drive… would do again.

Big thanks to Misha and Apex for the car and driving points 🏆

Getting reminders from shooting Electrikhana this time last year, thanks @doitforbmoore and @pierrewikberg. 

A lot of great moments with @kblock43 were like this one: It’s 3AM in Vegas, and we just finished “lunch” on our all-night shoot. Ken’s Sport Quattro build recently got finished, and he hadn’t really thrown it around yet. He had the keys, I had my phone, and we got this clip in the parking lot - about 20 feet from the catering setup. Nothing like making Group B car noises in the early morning hours.

Evo before/after + first ever yard test + a peek at the car’s new 2pc @motegiracing wheels. Biiig progress this year.

@hertlife sent me that top shot from 2019 to remind me how far this thing has come from the wrecked heap that it was. There were so many points over the last 3 years where I was ready to just part it out, but the support on this build is next level. 

Dialing in diff and suspension balance is next, but overall the car doing what I always envisioned it to do. Feelsgoodman.

If you’ve read this far - something something never give up / follow your dreams / live laugh love

Fresh wrap! Did some gloss black and carbon blend recently with those @seiboncarbon doors / fenders / hood. 

It’s so weird seeing the Evo in all one color for the first time in years, especially not ‘test car white’. But I’m getting it ready for this year’s SEMA and SEMA Fest shows, so I can’t be hiding all that weave

Life update: I’m starting a new chapter after 13 years of the wildest journey ever with Hoonigan. 

From seeing the brand start as just a logo on a laptop in @brianscotto’s BK loft, to watching @hertlife @vin_tra @mister_zachary @jchase7452 @brandonkado and the rest of the crew take it to a crazy level on YouTube with Daily Transmission, then joining the LA team fully in 2018 - the brand grew bigger than I ever could have imagined. Super thankful for everything the brand has taught me over the years.

Here’s to 2024 ⚡️
